Koding



Under ligger kodingen som hÃ¸rer til ui-delen av shinyApp. Den baserer seg hovedsaklig pÃ¥ koding allerede gjort. Viser likevel disse dersom det skulle vÃ¦re Ã¸nskelig Ã¥ kjÃ¸re dette i egen R da de mÃ¥ brukes i ui.R.

################################################
# Dette er mye koding som allerede er gjort i innleveringen, under OPPG3.
# FÃ¸rst er det for pruduktene vi vil sammenligne.
# Da mye av kodebruken er den samme som tidligere, kommenterer vi 
# bare det som gjÃ¸es for fÃ¸rste gang her.
March_Month_Store_24 <- Sandwich_df %>%
  ungroup() %>% 
  dplyr::filter(Store_Num == 24) %>%
  dplyr::filter_all(any_vars(grepl("2013-03",Date)))

March_Store_24<- March_Month_Store_24 %>%
  dplyr::select(Date,Sold,Description,Profit)

March_Store_24 <- March_Store_24[!duplicated(March_Store_24), ]

March_Store_24 <- March_Store_24 %>%
  group_by(Date) %>%
  mutate(Tot_Profit = sum(Profit))
##########################################
February_Month_Store_24 <- Sandwich_df %>%
  ungroup() %>% 
  dplyr::filter(Store_Num == 24) %>%
  dplyr::filter_all(any_vars(grepl("2013-02",Date)))

February_Store_24<- February_Month_Store_24 %>%
  dplyr::select(Date,Sold,Description,Profit)

February_Store_24 <- February_Store_24[!duplicated(February_Store_24), ]

February_Store_24 <- February_Store_24 %>%
  group_by(Date) %>%
  mutate(Tot_Profit = sum(Profit))
##########################################

Pizza_And_Veggie_Sold <- rbind(February_Store_24,March_Store_24)

Pizza_And_Veggie_Sold <- Pizza_And_Veggie_Sold %>%
  dplyr::select(Date, Description, Sold) %>%
  dplyr::filter_all(any_vars(grepl("PIZZA|VEGGIE",Description)))

Pizza_And_Veggie_Sold_Wide <- Pizza_And_Veggie_Sold %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = Description,
              values_from = Sold)

Pizza_And_Veggie_Sold_Wide [is.na(Pizza_And_Veggie_Sold_Wide )] <- 0

######################################################
# Dette er for prudukter. Vi var nÃ¸dt til Ã¥ bruke pivot_wider.
All_Dates_Store_24_filtrert<- All_Dates_Store_24_1 %>%
  dplyr::select(Date, Description, Sold) %>%
  dplyr::filter_all(any_vars(grepl("PIZZA|VEGGIE",Description)))

All_Dates_Store_24_filtrert<- All_Dates_Store_24_filtrert %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = Description,
              values_from = Sold)

All_Dates_Store_24_filtrert[is.na(All_Dates_Store_24_filtrert)] <- 0

# Hadde vell strengt talt ikke trengt Ã¥ gjÃ¸re dette pÃ¥ nytt med dato,
# Men gjorde det likevel for sikrets skyld.
All_Dates_Store_24_filtrert$Date <- as.Date(All_Dates_Store_24_filtrert$Date, format = "%Y.%m.%d")

All_Dates_Store_24_filtrert = All_Dates_Store_24_filtrert %>%
  mutate(Date = ymd(Date)) %>%
  mutate_at(vars(Date), funs(year, month, day))
############################################
# Dette er for Ã¥ finne kostnader.
All_Dates_Store_24 <- Sandwich_df %>%
  dplyr::filter(Store_Num == 24) %>%
  dplyr::select(Date,Description,Sold,Profit,Annual_Rent_Estimate,Cost,Year,Month)

All_Dates_Store_24_1 <- All_Dates_Store_24[!duplicated(All_Dates_Store_24),]

# Dette er ogsÃ¥ for kostnader
All_Dates_Store_24_2 <- All_Dates_Store_24[!duplicated(All_Dates_Store_24),]
# Vi delte annual rent pÃ¥ 52 da den sÃ¥ ut til Ã¥ vÃ¦re ukentlig
All_Dates_Store_24_2 <- All_Dates_Store_24_2 %>%
  group_by(Date) %>%
  mutate(Cost_Term = sum(Cost) + (15000 / 52)) %>%
  ungroup(Date) %>%
  distinct(Date,Cost_Term,Year, Month)

# Deretter brukes aggregate med hjelp av Month og Year til Ã¥ summere fra uker til mÃ¥ned.
output24<- aggregate(Cost_Term ~ Month + Year,
                     All_Dates_Store_24_2,
                     FUN = sum)
# Gj@r mÃ¥ned og Ã¥r med lubridate::make_date om til Date for DataTable i shiny
output24<-output24 %>% 
  mutate(Date = make_date(Year,Month)) %>% 
  select(Date, Cost_Term)

output24<-output24 %>% 
  mutate_if(is.numeric, round, digits = 2)
  
#############################################
# Denne delen hÃ¸rer til mÃ¥nedlig profit der vi vil sammenligne med ande
# mÃ¥neder.
Rapport <- Utsalgsted_24 %>%
  ungroup() 

# Velger Ã¸nsket kolonner
Rapport_24<- Rapport %>%
  select(Date,Sold,Profit,Description,Year, Month)

# Fjerner duplikasjons-verdier
Rapport_24 <- Rapport_24[!duplicated(Rapport_24), ]

# Grupperer by Date og summerer profit i mutate().
Rapport_24 <- Rapport_24 %>%
  group_by(Date) %>%
  mutate(Tot_Profit = sum(Profit))

# Summerer ukes-profittene til en samlet mÃ¥nedlig profit. 
Month_Total_Profit <- Rapport_24[!duplicated(Rapport_24$Tot_Profit), ]
Month_Total_Profit_Table<-Month_Total_Profit %>% 
  select(Date, Tot_Profit, Year, Month) %>% 
  ungroup()
# GjÃ¸r samme type aggregate som tidligere, men for Tot_Profit
Month_Total_Profit_Table_24<- aggregate(Tot_Profit ~ Month + Year,
                                        Month_Total_Profit_Table,
                                        FUN = sum)
# bruker igjen lubridate::make_date
Month_Total_Profit_Table_24<-Month_Total_Profit_Table_24 %>% 
  mutate(Date = make_date(Year,Month)) %>% 
  select(Date, Tot_Profit)

################################# Her begynner server delen #################################
server <- function(input, output) {
   # FÃ¸rst her, er plottet for produkter
  plotfunct <- reactive({
   if (input$Tredje)
     { ggplot(data = Pizza_And_Veggie_Sold_Wide, aes_string(x = input$Date, y = input$Menu))+ 
        geom_line(color = "springgreen", alpha = 0.85, lwd = 1.5)+ 
        geom_point(stat = "identity", color = "royalblue", alpha = 0.85,size =3) + 
        scale_x_date(date_breaks = "1 week") +
        labs(x = "",
             y = "Total Number sold",
             title = "Pizza And Veggie Items\nSold This Month Compared To Last Month",
             color = "Menu Item")+
        theme(text=element_text(family = "Times New Roman"),
              plot.title = element_text(colour = "dodgerblue4", hjust = 0.5, size = 16),
              axis.title.y = element_text(colour = "dodgerblue4"), 
              axis.title.x = element_text(colour = "dodgerblue4"),
              axis.ticks = element_line(colour = "aliceblue"),
              axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90),
              axis.text.x.bottom = element_text(colour = "darkslategray4"),
              axis.text.y.left = element_text(colour = "darkslategray4"),
              panel.background = element_rect(fill = "white", colour = "grey85"), 
              panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = "aliceblue"), 
              panel.grid.minor = element_line(colour = "azure"))
    }
  })
  output$plot1 <- renderPlot({
    plotfunct()
  })
  output$datatable <-renderDataTable({#i ui la vi til Ã¸nsket datatable,
    Pizza_And_Veggie_Sold_Wide        #her sier vi hvordan datatable.
  })
  #Her er plottet for kostnader.
plotfunct3 <- reactive({
  output24_1 <- output24 %>%
    dplyr::filter(grepl(input$Termin, Date))
  
  output24_1 %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = Date, y = Cost_Term, fill(Date))) + 
    geom_col(col = "springgreen4", width= 10, alpha = 0.50, fill = "royalblue") + 
    labs(x = "",
         y = "",
         title = "Cost Per Month")+
    theme(text=element_text(family = "Times New Roman"),
          plot.title = element_text(colour = "dodgerblue4", hjust = 0.5, size = 16),
          axis.title.y = element_text(colour = "dodgerblue4"), 
          axis.title.x = element_text(colour = "dodgerblue4"),
          axis.ticks = element_line(colour = "aliceblue"),
          axis.text.x.bottom = element_text(colour = "darkslategray4"),
          axis.text.y.left = element_text(colour = "darkslategray4"),
          panel.background = element_rect(fill = "white", colour = "grey85"), 
          panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = "aliceblue"), 
          panel.grid.minor = element_line(colour = "azure"))
  
  
})


output$plot3 <- renderPlot({
  plotfunct3()
  
})
#Dette er plottet for endring i profit fra mÃ¥ned til mÃ¥ned.
plotfunct4 <- reactive({
  Stolpe1 <- Month_Total_Profit_Table_24 %>%
    filter(grepl(input$Year,Date))
  #Siden valgmulighetene skulle vÃ¦re tilstede.
  Stolpe2 <- Month_Total_Profit_Table_24 %>%
    filter(grepl(input$Year2, Date))
  
  # rbindes fÃ¸r plot
  Stolpe3 <- rbind(Stolpe1, Stolpe2)
  
  ggplot(data = Stolpe3, aes(x = Date, y = Tot_Profit, fill(Date)))+
    geom_col(col = "springgreen4", width= 10, alpha = 0.50, fill = "royalblue")+
    labs(x = "",
         y = "Profit In $",
         title = "Changes in Profit by\nCustom Selected Month`s") + 
    theme(text=element_text(family = "Times New Roman"),
          plot.title = element_text(colour = "dodgerblue4", hjust = 0.5, size = 15),
          axis.title.y = element_text(colour = "dodgerblue4"), 
          axis.title.x = element_text(colour = "dodgerblue4"),
          axis.ticks = element_line(colour = "aliceblue"),
          axis.text.x.bottom = element_text(colour = "darkslategray4"),
          axis.text.y.left = element_text(colour = "darkslategray4"),
          panel.background = element_rect(fill = "white", colour = "grey85"), 
          panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = "aliceblue"), 
          panel.grid.minor = element_line(colour = "azure"))
  
})

output$datatable3 <-renderDataTable({
  Month_Total_Profit_Table_24
})


output$datatable2 <-renderDataTable({
  output24
})
output$plot4 <- renderPlot({
  plotfunct4()
})



},
